<TITLE> Shah Rukh Khan stars in reincarnation saga </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, Sep 22 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Bell-bottoms and sideburns will make a comeback in a new Bollywood film about reincarnation in which superstar heart-throb Shah Rukh Khan plays an actor who comes back from the dead. Directed by Farah Khan, 'Om Shanti Om' is the story of a young, talented actor in the 1970s who falls for a superstar but dies before he can win her love. He is then reborn, this time as a successful actor in present-day Bollywood, but one who has to rely on his macho image, rather than his talent, to succeed. "The film is about reincarnation in which I play two different roles," Khan, one of India's biggest stars, said at a promotional event late on Tuesday. 'Om Shanti Om' recreates 1970s Bollywood and the fashion of the era -- bell-bottoms, applique saris, long-collared shirts, sideburns and matted backbrush. 'Om Shanti Om' is scheduled to open in Novemb
